#: ../../P/perfect-programmer-syndrome.rst:5
msgid "perfect programmer syndrome"
msgstr "perfect programmer syndrome"

#: ../../P/perfect-programmer-syndrome.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../P/perfect-programmer-syndrome.rst:9
msgid ""
"Arrogance; the egotistical conviction that one is above normal human error. "
"Most frequently found among programmers of some native ability but "
"relatively little experience (especially new graduates; their perceptions "
"may be distorted by a history of excellent performance at solving :ref:`toy-"
"problem`\\s). \"Of course my program is correct, there is no need to test "
"it.\" \"Yes, I can see there may be a problem here, but I'll never type "
":code:`rm -r /` while in :ref:`root-mode`\\.\""
msgstr ""
"傲慢さ。自分は通常の人間的なミスを超越しているという自己中心的な確信。生来のいくらかの能力はあるが比較的経験の乏しいプログラマ(特に新卒者。彼らの認識は、\\"
" :ref:`toy-problem`\\ "
"を解くことでの優秀な成績の経歴によって歪んでいるかもしれない)の間に最も頻繁に見られる。「もちろん僕のプログラムは正しい。テストする必要はない」「ああ、ここに問題があるかもしれないのはわかるが、\\"
" :ref:`root-mode`\\ にいるときに\\ :code:`rm -r /`\\ なんて絶対にタイプしないよ」"
